library(data.table)
library(dplyr)
library(ggplot2)
library(tidyr)
library(GGally)
library(forcats)

library(modeest)   
library(stringr)

Carga y Limpieza Inicial

columnas_importantes <- c("genres", "original_language", "adult",
                          "vote_average", "vote_count", "revenue",
                          "budget", "runtime", "popularity")
datos <- fread("datos.csv", select = columnas_importantes)

datos$genres <- as.character(datos$genres) 
datos$original_language <- as.character(datos$original_language)
datos$adult <- as.character(datos$adult)

datos_limpios <- datos %>%
  filter(!(vote_average == 0 & vote_count == 0)) %>%
  filter(!is.na(genres), !is.na(original_language), !is.na(adult)) %>%
  separate_rows(genres, sep = ",\\s*")

— Gráficos y Análisis Anteriores —

##Genero

tabla_generos <- datos_limpios %>% # Usar datos_limpios para gráficos basados en géneros separados por comas
  filter(!is.na(genres) & genres != "") %>% 
  count(genres, sort = TRUE) %>%
  head(10)

ggplot(tabla_generos, aes(x = reorder(genres, n), y = n)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", fill = "steelblue") +
  coord_flip() +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(title = "Top 10 géneros más frecuentes",
       x = "Género",
       y = "Cantidad de películas")

Idioma Original

tabla_idioma <- datos_limpios %>% # Puede usar datos_limpios o datos, el idioma no se modifica
  filter(!is.na(original_language) & original_language != "") %>% 
  count(original_language, sort = TRUE) %>%
  head(10)

ggplot(tabla_idioma, aes(x = reorder(original_language, n), y = n)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", fill = "red") +
  coord_flip() +
  theme_minimal() +

       x = "Idioma Original",
       y = "Cantidad de películas")

Barra agrupada: original_language vs adult

top_10_idiomas_agrup <- datos_limpios %>% # Usar datos_limpios o datos
  count(original_language, sort = TRUE) %>%
  head(10) %>%
  pull(original_language)

datos_agrupados <- datos_limpios %>% # Usar datos_limpios o datos
  filter(original_language %in% top_10_idiomas_agrup)

ggplot(datos_agrupados, aes(x = original_language, fill = adult)) +
  geom_bar(position = "dodge") +
  labs(title = "Películas por idioma y clasificación adulta",
       x = "Idioma Original", y = "Cantidad") +
  theme_minimal()

Barra apilada Genre vs Original Language

top_10_idiomas_apil <- datos_limpios %>% # Usar datos_limpios
  count(original_language, sort = TRUE) %>%
  head(10) %>%
  pull(original_language)

datos_apilados <- datos_limpios %>% # Usar datos_limpios

ggplot(datos_apilados, aes(x = original_language, fill = genres)) +

Calcular media y desviación estándar sin los ceros (para la curva normal)

media <- mean(datos_limpios$vote_average, na.rm = TRUE)
desv <- sd(datos_limpios$vote_average, na.rm = TRUE)

Histograma calificacion promedio con curva normal superpuesta

ggplot(datos_limpios, aes(x = vote_average)) +
  geom_histogram(aes(y = ..density..), bins = 30, fill = "mediumturquoise", alpha = 0.5) +
  stat_function(fun = dnorm, args = list(mean = media, sd = desv), color = "red", size = 1) +
  labs(
    title = "Distribución de vote_average (sin ceros) con curva normal",
    x = "Calificacion promedio",
    y = "Densidad"
  ) +
  theme_minimal()

budget por género (top 5 únicos géneros)

top_generos <- datos_limpios %>%
  group_by(genres) %>%
  summarise(count = n()) %>%
  top_n(5, count) %>%
  pull(genres)

ggplot(datos_limpios %>% filter(genres %in% top_generos),
       aes(x = fct_reorder(genres, budget, .fun = median, .desc = TRUE), y = budget, fill = genres)) +
  geom_boxplot(alpha = 0.7) + # Puede generar warnings si hay budget <= 0 y se usa escala log
  labs(title = "Presupuesto por género (Top 5)",
       x = "Género", y = "Presupuesto (USD)") +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(legend.position = "none") #+

Revenue promedio por idioma (top 5)

top_5_idiomas <- datos_limpios %>%
  count(original_language, sort = TRUE) %>%
  head(5) %>%
  pull(original_language)
datos_filtrado <- datos_limpios %>% filter(original_language %in% top_5_idiomas)

datos_filtrado %>%
  group_by(original_language) %>%
  summarise(prom_revenue = mean(revenue, na.rm = TRUE),
            sd_revenue = sd(revenue, na.rm = TRUE),
            n = n(),
            se = sd_revenue / sqrt(n)) %>% # Usar la n calculada
  ggplot(aes(x = fct_reorder(original_language, prom_revenue),
             y = prom_revenue)) +
  geom_col(fill = "#69b3a2") +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = prom_revenue - se, ymax = prom_revenue + se), width = 0.2) +
  labs(title = "Ingresos promedio por idioma original (Top 5)",
       x = "Idioma original", y = "Ingreso promedio (USD)") +
  theme_minimal() +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::label_number(scale = 1e-6, suffix = "M")) # Escala en millones

Prueba de Hipotesis ##Prueba de hipótesis para la variable cuantitativa vote_average

t.test(datos_limpios$vote_average, mu = 7, alternative = "less")
## 
##  One Sample t-test
## 
## data:  datos_limpios$vote_average
## t = -366.01, df = 566370, p-value < 2.2e-16
## alternative hypothesis: true mean is less than 7

Prueba de hipótesis para la variable categorica adult

n_total_limpios <- nrow(datos_limpios) 
n_adultos_limpios <- sum(datos_limpios$adult == "TRUE", na.rm = TRUE) # Asegúrate que el valor sea "TRUE" exactamente

prop.test(x = n_adultos_limpios, n = n_total_limpios, p = 0.05, alternative = "greater")
## 
##  1-sample proportions test with continuity correction
## 
## data:  n_adultos_limpios out of n_total_limpios, null probability 0.05
## X-squared = 1956, df = 1, p-value = 1
## alternative hypothesis: true p is greater than 0.05
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  0.03677891 1.00000000

##          p 
## 0.03719117

Estadigrafos

estadigraficos_genero <- datos_limpios %>%
  
  group_by(genres) %>% 
  filter(genres != "") %>% 
  summarise(
    n = n(),

    # budget
    presupuesto_media = mean(budget, na.rm = TRUE),
    presupuesto_mediana = median(budget, na.rm = TRUE),
    presupuesto_sd = sd(budget, na.rm = TRUE),
    presupuesto_cv = ifelse(mean(budget, na.rm = TRUE) != 0 & !is.na(mean(budget, na.rm = TRUE)), 
                            sd(budget, na.rm = TRUE) / mean(budget, na.rm = TRUE), 
                            NA), 
    presupuesto_asimetria = e1071::skewness(budget, na.rm = TRUE),
    presupuesto_curtosis = e1071::kurtosis(budget, na.rm = TRUE),
    presupuesto_Q1 = quantile(budget, probs = 0.25, na.rm = TRUE),
    presupuesto_Q2 = quantile(budget, probs = 0.50, na.rm = TRUE),
    presupuesto_Q3 = quantile(budget, probs = 0.75, na.rm = TRUE),
    
    # revenue
    revenue_media = mean(revenue, na.rm = TRUE),
    revenue_mediana = median(revenue, na.rm = TRUE),
    revenue_sd = sd(revenue, na.rm = TRUE),
    revenue_cv = ifelse(mean(revenue, na.rm = TRUE) != 0 & !is.na(mean(revenue, na.rm = TRUE)),
                        sd(revenue, na.rm = TRUE) / mean(revenue, na.rm = TRUE),
                        NA),
    revenue_asimetria = e1071::skewness(revenue, na.rm = TRUE),
    revenue_curtosis = e1071::kurtosis(revenue, na.rm = TRUE),
    revenue_Q1 = quantile(revenue, probs = 0.25, na.rm = TRUE),
    revenue_Q2 = quantile(revenue, probs = 0.50, na.rm = TRUE),
    revenue_Q3 = quantile(revenue, probs = 0.75, na.rm = TRUE),
    
    # runtime
    runtime_media = mean(runtime, na.rm = TRUE),
    runtime_mediana = median(runtime, na.rm = TRUE),
    runtime_sd = sd(runtime, na.rm = TRUE),
    runtime_cv = ifelse(mean(runtime, na.rm = TRUE) != 0 & !is.na(mean(runtime, na.rm = TRUE)),
                        sd(runtime, na.rm = TRUE) / mean(runtime, na.rm = TRUE),
                        NA),
    runtime_asimetria = e1071::skewness(runtime, na.rm = TRUE),
    runtime_curtosis = e1071::kurtosis(runtime, na.rm = TRUE),
    runtime_Q1 = quantile(runtime, probs = 0.25, na.rm = TRUE),
    runtime_Q2 = quantile(runtime, probs = 0.50, na.rm = TRUE),
    runtime_Q3 = quantile(runtime, probs = 0.75, na.rm = TRUE),
    
    # vote_average 
    vote_average_media = mean(vote_average, na.rm = TRUE),
    vote_average_mediana = median(vote_average, na.rm = TRUE),
    vote_average_sd = sd(vote_average, na.rm = TRUE),
    vote_average_cv = ifelse(mean(vote_average, na.rm = TRUE) != 0 & !is.na(mean(vote_average, na.rm = TRUE)), 
                             sd(vote_average, na.rm = TRUE) / mean(vote_average, na.rm = TRUE), 
                             NA), 
    vote_average_asimetria = e1071::skewness(vote_average, na.rm = TRUE),
    vote_average_curtosis = e1071::kurtosis(vote_average, na.rm = TRUE),
    vote_average_Q1 = quantile(vote_average, probs = 0.25, na.rm = TRUE),
    vote_average_Q2 = quantile(vote_average, probs = 0.50, na.rm = TRUE),
    vote_average_Q3 = quantile(vote_average, probs = 0.75, na.rm = TRUE),
    
    # popularity 
    popularity_media = mean(popularity, na.rm = TRUE),
    popularity_mediana = median(popularity, na.rm = TRUE),
    popularity_sd = sd(popularity, na.rm = TRUE),
    popularity_cv = ifelse(mean(popularity, na.rm = TRUE) != 0 & !is.na(mean(popularity, na.rm = TRUE)), 
                           sd(popularity, na.rm = TRUE) / mean(popularity, na.rm = TRUE), 
                           NA), 
    popularity_asimetria = e1071::skewness(popularity, na.rm = TRUE),
    popularity_curtosis = e1071::kurtosis(popularity, na.rm = TRUE),
    popularity_Q1 = quantile(popularity, probs = 0.25, na.rm = TRUE),
    popularity_Q2 = quantile(popularity, probs = 0.50, na.rm = TRUE),
    popularity_Q3 = quantile(popularity, probs = 0.75, na.rm = TRUE),
    
    .groups = 'drop' 
  ) %>%
  arrange(genres)
